If you are using the "Normal" or "Yesterday/Today" settings for Datestamp Display, enter the format you wish to use for the display of dates here. This follows PHP's <a href="http://www.php.net/date" target="_blank">date function formatting options</a>.<br /><br />

Some examples:<br />
m-d-y becomes 04-25-98 (Standard short US format)<br />
F jS, Y becomes April 25th, 1998 (Standard long US format)<br />
d-m-Y becomes 25-04-98 (Standard short European format)<br />
jS F Y becomes 25th April 1998 (Standard long European format)